article.headline: Buffalo 81, Evansville 60
article.story: AMHERST, NY. (AP) -- Sean Smiley scored 14 points, including four 3-pointers, helping lead Buffalo to an 81-60 win over Evansville Saturday. Evansville's Shy Ely scored a game-high 22 points. Ely was 10-of-16 from the field with five rebounds, but the rest of the Purple Aces continued their season-long struggle from the floor. Evansville shot just 39.6 percent, and aside from Ely's night the Aces converted just 11-of-37 shots. Jason Holsinger scored 11 points with five assists while Nate Garner grabbed eight rebounds. Both teams opened poorly, as Buffalo and Evansville combined to shoot 4-of-12 with 14 turnovers in the first seven minutes. Holsinger's 3-pointer gave the Aces a 15-14 lead, and Darrin Granger brought Evansville even at 23-23 with 3:30 left in the half. But Smiley sparked a 10-2 run and the Bulls held a 37-28 lead at halftime. A slam dunk by Andy Robinson set the tone for Buffalo's second-half opening 8-2 run. The Aces got as close as 47-39 before Buffalo opened up a 19-point lead during which Evansville shot just 8-of-22. Buffalo was 29-of-49 (59.2 percent) from the floor, 16-of-19 from the foul line.
